  "prompt": "What are the top 10 countries of Instagram users?",
  "response": "As of the most recent data available (up to October 2023), here are the **top 10 countries** with the highest number of Instagram users:\n\n1. **United States**  \n   - Instagram's largest user base with over **143 million users**.  \n   - Popular for influencers, brands, and celebrities.\n\n2. **India**  \n   - Second-largest user base with over **130 million users**.  \n   - Rapid growth due to increasing smartphone and internet penetration.\n\n3. **Brazil**  \n   - Third-largest user base with over **110 million users**.  \n   - High engagement rates and strong influencer culture.\n\n4. **Indonesia**  \n   - Fourth-largest user base with over **90 million users**.  \n   - Dominated by younger demographics and social media enthusiasts.\n\n5. **Russia**  \n   - Fifth-largest user base with over **60 million users**.  \n   - Popular for both personal and business use.\n\n6. **Japan**  \n   - Sixth-largest user base with over **55 million users**.  \n   - Strong adoption among younger generations and businesses.\n\n7. **Mexico**  \n   - Seventh-largest user base with over **50 million users**.  \n   - Growing rapidly with high social media engagement.\n\n8. **Turkey**  \n   - Eighth-largest user base with over **45 million users**.  \n   - Popular for lifestyle, travel, and influencer content.\n\n9. **United Kingdom**  \n   - Ninth-largest user base with over **40 million users**.  \n   - High adoption among millennials and Gen Z.\n\n10. **Germany**  \n    - Tenth-largest user base with over **35 million users**.  \n    - Growing popularity among younger demographics and businesses.\n\nThese rankings can fluctuate over time due to changes in internet accessibility, platform popularity, and demographic shifts. Instagram's global user base exceeds **2 billion monthly active users**, making it one of the most widely used social media platforms worldwide.",
